      <bioghist id="aspace_88eaed1b182b3d6b2d71a304605834a6">
         <head>William Morris (1834-1896)</head>
         <p>William Morris was an English designer, artist, writer, and socialist associated with the Pre-Raphaelite Brotherhood and the English Arts and Crafts Movement.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_ab83a9fb099ccfe5852b7ee51f318a62">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection consists of seven letters written by William Morris to friends and acquaintances, and a group of autograph manuscripts by him. One manuscript, "The Wood Beyond the World," is accompanied by a drawing made for the book by Sir Edward Coley Burne-Jones, and two impressions of the resulting engraving.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_aa5d04dd24c7cab7e5d92160aac15eb1">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into two series: I. Letters, 1870-1891. II. Writings, 1870-1895.</p>  
      </arrangement>
